3759, "Terran Gauntlet"

3760, "The player runs the Gauntlet against an ever-increasing rush of Terrans.  Exciting, isn't it?"

3761, "While you were able to survive the first phase of Terran enemies, you were unable to meet the challenge presented to you by the other waves.  Your performance was what we would expect from a rookie fresh from flight school."

3762, "You were able to survive two phases of Terran enemies before you evacuated the Gauntlet.  This was a marginally satisfactory performance, one that we might expect from an Alliance reserve pilot."

3763, "You conquered three phases of Terran fighters before conceding defeat.  You performed well and with honor.  If you ever feel particularly adventurous, you might want to attempt to defeat all of the ships in the Gauntlet.  Well done, Pilot."

3764, "You almost ran the entire Gauntlet, Pilot.  Excellent job.  Very few pilots could ever hope to emulate your accomplishment.  We are definitely going to keep our eye on you, Pilot.  You might want to consider meeting the final challenge of the Gauntlet sometime in the future.  Dismissed."

3765, "You successfully ran the Gauntlet, Pilot!  Congratulations!  Your skill will inspire confidence in your fellow pilots and in the Alliance.  Good job."

; V-Gauntlet.fs2

3766, "Vasudan Gauntlet"

3767, "The player runs the Gauntlet against an ever-increasing rush of Vasudans."

3768, "There will be 5 waves of Vasudan enemies.  Each wave will be comprised of 3 to 6 groups of enemy ships.  After clearing the final wave, you will have run the Gauntlet.  Doing so will win you a certain level of honor and privilege within the League of Defense.  Good luck, Pilot."

3769, "You conquered three phases of Vasudan fighters before conceding defeat.  You performed well and with honor.  If you ever feel particularly adventurous, you might want to attempt to defeat all of the ships in the Gauntlet.  Well done, Pilot."

3770, "You successfully ran the Gauntlet, Pilot!  Congratulations!  Your performance was truly amazing.  To recognize your skill as a fighter pilot, the Alliance will send you into tremendously risky and dangerous battle situations.  Your courage inspires confidence in your fellow pilots and in the Alliance.  Again, a most excellent job, Pilot."

3771, "Your hull can't take much more, Pilot.  You may exit the Gauntlet without fear of losing honor, if you wish."

